added.title: Opposites
added.description: Cyborg has a star-crossed crush on Jinx, the cutest member of The Hive.

added.title: Be Mine
added.description: Beast Boy invites Tara to the Titan's Valentine's Day dance and she accepts in order to destroy all of the Titans and exact revenge on Beast Boy.

added.title: Love Monsters
added.description: Despite Raven's warnings, Starfire showers love on the adorable twin destroyers of the universe.

added.title: How 'Bout Some Effort
added.description: It's Valentine's Day and Cyborg goes to great lengths to make it special for his girlfriend Jinx.

added.title: BBRAE Part 1
added.description: Beast Boy writes a song to tell Raven how he feels about her.

added.title: The Misunderstandings
added.description: Gumball has misunderstood about his date with Penny. He thought they were meeting for dinner but they were actually meeting for lunch at a Diner called Dinner. He runs to the mall but everyone he meets on the way seems to misunderstand him in a different way. Once he finally does get to the mall, it seems all his misunderstandings have caught up with him.

added.title: The Matchmaker
added.description: Gumball catches Darwin gazing wistfully at a photo of Teri on Elmore Plus and secretly enlists Carrie to help bring them together. But when they can't make Darwin and Teri's love blossom naturally, they decide to make it happen supernaturally.

added.title: The Heart
added.description: When Mr. Robinson accidentally let slip how little he cares for Gumball and Darwin, they react by giving him the cold shoulder.  Surprisingly Mr. Robinson misses them and tries to win back their friendship. After a few failed attempts, Gumball and Darwin realize that Mr. Robinson's heart is protecting him, so they give it an intense affection overload.

added.title: The Question
added.description: Gumball and Darwin seek the answer to the biggest question of all: what is the meaning of life? They need to understand the point of their lives, so resolve to seek advice from everyone in Elmore. They ask people, animals and even planets but their answer comes from an unexpected source.

added.title: The Saint
added.description: Gumball doesn't believe anyone could really be as nice as Alan and sets out to find his breaking point. Alan is so good-natured that Gumball feels compelled to make him lose his temper. Despite turning the whole school against him, destroying his relationship with Carmen and even selling his parents, Alan remains understanding and happy. Defeated, Gumball and Darwin decide to adopt Alan's positive attitude to see if they can be more like Alan.Gumball and Darwin help Anais make up an imaginary friend who turns out to be all too real. Anais throws a party but no-one shows up as she has no friends or social skills. Gumball and Darwin help Anais make up an imaginary friend who, much to all their surprise, appears in front of them. Gumball and Darwin teach Anais and her new friend how to become friends but realize he might not be so imaginary after all.

added.title: The Rise and Fall of the Green Poncho
added.description: Craig tries to warn his friends about the Other Side of the Creek with a tale from the Creek's defender - the Green Poncho.

added.title: I Don't Need a Hat
added.description: Craig decides to ditch his hat on a chilly day and it becomes a battle for body heat.

added.title: Alternate Creekiverse
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP imagine a disturbing alternate reality where they never became friends!

added.title: Mooshy Mon Mons
added.description: After eating Chef's extremely rare and expensive chocolates Courtney drags Owen, Izzy and Beth all the way to the Norberian Alps of Fruffenberg to replace them.

added.title: Student Becomes the Teacher
added.description: Chef is knocked unconscious right before a School Board Evaluator shows up for a big review. Now Owen has to fill in so Chef doesn't lose his Teaching License and to ensure the kids earn the pony ride Chef promised for good behavior.

added.title: Beth and the Beanstalk
added.description: After having a chocolate bar confiscated by Chef, Beth finds herself in a parallel giant world and aims to get back her now giant chocolate bar.

added.title: Pinata Regatta
added.description: Izzy can't bring herself to smash a Pinata during the class' Cinco De Mayo celebrations. But when that unsmashed Pinata comes to life and spawns an evil Pinata Army, it's batter up.

added.title: A Dame-gerous Game
added.description: After Leshawna, Bridgette, Owen and Cody win a Hide & Seek competition, they're trapped on a private island by a jealous former champion and forced to play for their freedom.

added.title: Escape From Bebe Bay
added.description: When Vic & Val accidentally turn themselves and Don into babies, they must escape a daycare center in order to change back to their normal ages.

added.title: Band For Life
added.description: When Vic and Val tag along with Xochi to a punk concert, they want to prove that they're cool enough to hang out with her. But in a desperate attempt to be cool, they wind up destroying the concert.

added.title: Tez Says
added.description: Vic & Val are in awe of the new magician in town, but things go awry when they agree to help him out with a new trick - despite Chata's wishes.

added.title: Forever Ever
added.description: When Vic and Val do a sloppy job cleaning up in Maria Theresa's attic, they accidentally set off a time loop, trapping them in an endless series of chores forever! They must figure out how to stop the loop and return time back to normal.

added.title: Dance Reynaldo Dance
added.description: Vic is desperate to win the cash prize for the dance contest in Monte Macabre and is frustrated that his partner Val won't let him call all the shots. Instead he chooses a different partner: Reynaldo. But Vic pushes Reynaldo too hard to execute his artistic vision. Eventually he learns that in order to be a success, you have to be equal partners.

added.title: Hotdog's Movie Premiere
added.description: Apple and Onion square off against a no-nonsense security guard after they're banned from the premiere of their friend Hot Dog's new movie.

added.title: Bottle Catch
added.description: Apple and Onion's favorite game attracts some unexpected attention.

added.title: Pancake's Bus Tour
added.description: Apple and Onion go on a guided bus tour as part of their plan to get Apple's shoe back.

added.title: Jelly Wrestle Rumble!
added.description: Huckleberry Hound hosts a wrestling tournament so that his childhood hero, the Funky Phantom, can relive his glory days.

added.title: Hole in 10
added.description: While mini-golfing, Ben is attacked by the Ground Hawgs, a gang of Dr. Animo mutants turned bikers. When the Hawgs realize the faux mini-golf village isn't an actual town, Ben must go alien to stop them before they set their sights on the real city down the road.

added.title: Recipe for Disaster
added.description: During Chefapalooza in the Rocky Mountains, three famous chefs and infamous bad-guys, The Tri-Chefta, hunt down Wildvine in hopes of creating their most exotic dish to date.

added.title: Rustbucket RIP
added.description: During a tour of historic Oldeville Ben finds a rare Sumo Slammers card, but when Billy Billions comes to claim the same card Ben has to battle Billy's high-tech drones which have hijacked the Rust Bucket!

added.title: Freaky Gwen Ben
added.description: When Ben interferes with malicious magician Hex's quest for the earth-moving Titan Gloves at a swap meet, he inadvertently switches bodies with Gwen forcing him to walk a mile in her shoes and vice-versa!

added.title: Ben 24hrs
added.description: When Ben (and Gwen!) attempt to stay up all night for Adrenaland, the only theme park open 24/7, he not only fails to utilize his alien powers to stay awake, but his "sleep-alien-ing" causes disaster after disaster that Gwen must fix before things get way out of hand.

added.title: Video Date
added.description: Panda is an avid e-dater, and when a lovely French woman matches with him and agrees to a video chat date. Panda and his brothers engineer the situation so Panda is able to show the best side of himself on the video chat, even if that side of him is completely exaggerated.

added.title: Chloe and Ice Bear
added.description: On a day out with just Ice Bear, Chloe realizes Ice Bear only runs errands for his brothers. Determined to show him a fun day in the city, Chloe promises to help Ice Bear have a good time, even if it means staying  in a museum after it closes.

added.title: Panda's Date
added.description: When a vendor at the Farmer's Market (LUCY) sticks Panda with an EpiPen reviving him after an allergic reaction, Panda comes to in the arms of his dream girl. Panda tries to woo this woman of his dreams but his brothers and his own insecurities get in the way.

added.title: Summer Love
added.description: Panda goes on a mission to return a lost phone to the girl of his dreams.

added.title: Dance Lessons
added.description: Panda volunteers to be Lucy's partner for a dance contest. But Panda doesn't have the heart to tell Lucy that she's a terrible dancer.

added.title: Cry for Help
added.description: Steven's favorite TV show gets interrupted by a magical disturbance.

added.title: Keystone Motel
added.description: Steven, Greg and Garnet go on a road trip.

added.title: Onion Friend
added.description: Steven and Amethyst visit the strange world of Onion's house.

added.title: Historical Friction
added.description: Steven and Jamie put on a play about the founding of Beach City.

added.title: Friend Ship
added.description: The Crystal Gems explore an ancient Gem spaceship.

added.title: Hide N' Seek
added.description: Unikitty is proud to be the reigning champ of Hide N' Seek Day. But when Unikitty finds everyone in the kingdom except for Richard, she hunts him down at all costs. Will Richard continue to elude the Princess at her favorite game, and if so, how?!

added.title: Stuck Together
added.description: When Master Frown's head is stuck on Unikitty's butt, she vows to help him get his own body back, but first, she has to attend to her nice princess duties! But sharing a body with Master Frown can get pretty complicated, especially when Master Frown has his own agenda.

added.title: Little Prince Puppycorn
added.description: Puppycorn finally realizes he's a prince, so he wants to be in charge of the kingdom for once! Despite their friends' concerns, Unikitty makes Puppycorn ruler but realizes absolute power in the hands of the pup is too much for him to handle and his ideas aren't exactly great. Can they remove him from power while keeping the kingdom from revolting?

added.title: Pet Pet
added.description: Unikitty and the gang bring home a tiny creature they name Pet Pet, but Richard won't let them keep it if they can't prove they are responsible owners. But when Pet Pet runs away, Unikitty must pretend to be Pet Pet until they can find him, or Richard will never let them have Pet Pet (or any pet) ever again! Will Unikitty survive pet training, or finally admit responsibility is a lot harder than she thought?

added.title: Kitty Court
added.description: When Unikitty has a little auto incident with Master Frown, he insists on taking it to court! Frown's thrilled. There's nothing worse than boring old court and he can't wait to subject Unikitty to it! Unikitty is happy to make things right but the trial will be in Unikitty Court, which is so nonsensical and fun. It's Frown's worst nightmare! Will Master Frown succeed in bumming Unikitty out? Or will he be the one punished by their legal antics?

added.title: Second First Date
added.description: Love is in the air and Cupid arrives to resolve romantic tension around the plaza.

added.title: Rad Likes Robots
added.description: Rad finds love in an unexpected place.

added.title: My Fair Carol
added.description: KO, Enid and Rad team up to help Carol out with a special occasion.

added.title: K.O. vs Fink
added.description: When Fink taunts KO for being a momma's boy, he grapples with newfound insecurity about it.

added.title: You Are Rad
added.description: When KO forgets his name tag, Rad lets him use his, which results in everyone thinking KO is Rad, including Rad himself.

added.title: Arachno Romance
added.description: After the girls feel slighted by the Professor when he gets a new girlfriend, the girls conspire to break them up.

added.title: Monkey Love
added.description: When Blossom makes a bad call, she becomes afraid to try again.

added.title: Bridezilla
added.description: When Mojo and Barbarus announce their wedding, the girls are convinced that they're up to no good.

added.title: Can't Buy Love
added.description: When Morbucks falls in love, she finds the first thing money can't buy.

added.title: Musclecup
added.description: Feeling inadequate as a superhero, Buttercup bulks up…to the max.

added.title: Grudge Match
added.description: Ben and Kevin 11 are beamed up to a space ship where must learn to battle together in order to bring down a vicious alien fight promoter.

added.title: Camp Fear
added.description: When a race of alien mushrooms takes over a summer camp, Ben discovers a whole new alien to battle the menace.

added.title: Tough Luck
added.description: Gwen's Lucky Girl powers return when she buys a magical stone at a magic convention in Las Vegas. However, Hex is after the same stone, and after his niece breaks him out of prison, the two set off to retrieve the stone.

added.title: Mystery, Incorporeal
added.description: An old enemy emerges while Ben and Rook visit Kevin and Gwen at college.

added.title: An American Benwolf in London
added.description: Ben and Rook are called to London England to investigate the Forever Knights' latest activities.

added.title: Rad Monster Party
added.description: Ben and Rook enlist the help of intergalactic smuggler Rad Dudesman to fly them through the Anur System, the home of the monstrous aliens!

added.title: The Vampire Strikes Back
added.description: Ben, Rook, and Rad Dudesman come face to face with the evil Lord Transyl, a vampire-like alien who can make anyone his loyal slave! (Introducing new Ben alien, Whampire.)

added.title: And Then There Was Ben
added.description: Professor Paradox unites the good Bens from across all dimensions to take on Vilgax, Eon, and the evil Bens in the ultimate showdown!

added.title: Escape de Bahia Bebe
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic y Val se convierten a sí mismos y a Don en bebés, deben escapar de una guardería para poder volver a sus edades normales.

added.title: Banda de por Vida
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val acompañan a Xochi a un concierto punk, quieren demostrar que son lo suficientemente geniales para salir con ella. Pero en un intento desesperado por tener onda, terminan arruinando el concierto.

added.title: Tez dice
added.description: Vic y Val están impresionados con el nuevo mago de la ciudad, pero las cosas se complican cuando aceptan ayudarlo con un nuevo truco, a pesar de los deseos de Chata.

added.title: Eternamente
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val limpian el ático de María Teresa a medias, ipor accidente inician un bucle de tiempo que los atrapa en una serie interminable de tareas eternas! Ahora deben averiguar cómo detener el bucle y devolver el tiempo a la normalidad.

added.title: Baila Reynaldo Baila
added.description: Vic está desesperado por ganar el premio en efectivo para el concurso de baile en Monte Macabro y está frustrado porque Val, su pareja, no le deja tomar todas las decisiones. Por eso, elige un compañero diferente: Reynaldo. Pero Vic presiona demasiado a Reynaldo para hacer realidad su visión artística. Al final, Vic aprende que, para tener éxito, hay que ser socios en igualdad de condiciones.

added.title: Cherry Cream Soda
added.description: With the arrival of an impossible visitor, Cherry Cream Soda's life is thrown into disarray.

added.title: Just Friends
added.description: Rigby and Eileen get called away to Don's black belt ceremony forcing Mordecai and Margaret to hang out alone.

added.title: Rigby Goes to Prom
added.description: Rigby asks Eileen to prom. But in order to get there, he has to sneak his Dad's car out of the garage and get it back in one piece.

added.title: Dumped at the Altar
added.description: The guys have to get Muscle Man married.

added.title: The Suitor
added.description: Peppermint Butler thinks Princess Bubblegum is spending too much time in her lab and decides she needs a suitor.

added.title: Love Games
added.description: Slime Princess needs a husband or else she'll lose the Slime Kingdom to her obnoxious sis. Finn steps in to save the day but first they will need to win a series of love games to prove to Slime Princess's dad that they are really in love.

added.title: The Red Throne
added.description: When Flame King breaks out of his prison and takes over the Flame Kingdom again, Flame Princess turns to the one person she believes she can trust, Finn!

added.title: Uncle Cupid
added.description: Cupid, too lonely to perform his Valentine's Day duties, comes to Uncle Grandpa for help.

added.title: Burning Low
added.description: Finn starts spending a lot of time with Flame Princess. Is Princess Bubblegum jealous?

added.title: Valentimes
added.description: When Clarence notices his teacher Ms. Baker is the only one in class left without a Valentine this year, he decides to enlist the help of Sumo to set her up with Sumo's teacher, Mr. Mozer! Will sparks fly or will the boy's naive view of romance backfire?

added.title: Amor de verano
added.description: Panda se embarca en una misión para devolverle a la chica de sus sueños el teléfono que perdió.

added.title: Lecciones de Baile
added.description: Panda se ofrece como voluntario para ser el compañero de Lucy en un concurso de baile. Pero no se atreve a decirle a Lucy que es una pésima bailarina.

added.title: Mi Bella Carol
added.description: K.O., Enid y Rad se unen para ayudar a Carol para una ocasión especial.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Pretty Great Day with a Girl
added.description: Clarence and Amy, a unique girl from down the street, bond over a hunt for a monster-sized rock called an "erratic."

added.title: La Cita De Panda
added.description: Cuando una vendedora del Mercado de Granjeros (LUCY) le pone a Panda una inyección antialérgica que lo revive luego de una reacción alérgica, el Oso se despierta en los brazos de su chica soñada. Panda trata de conquistar a esta mujer de ensueño, pero sus hermanos y sus propias inseguridades se entrometen en el camino.

added.title: Clarence Gets a Girlfriend
added.description: When Clarence is asked out on a date by Ashley, a girl in his class, he realizes he doesn't know the first thing about having a girlfriend! Clarence enlists Sumo and Jeff to transform himself into the perfect gentleman just in time for his big date.

added.title: Meat Your Maker
added.description: After Rigby causes the guys to get locked in a meat locker, he must get help from some hot dogs in order to get them out.

added.title: Hot Dog Estrena su Pelicula
added.description: Cuando unos guardias de seguridad muy serios los echan del estreno de la nueva película de su amigo Hot Dog, Manzana y Cebollín se preparan para pelear.

added.title: Grilled Cheese Deluxe
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby lie about being astronauts in order to cut in line at a restaurant.

added.title: Atrapa la Botella
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín inventan un nuevo juego que atrae una atención inesperada.

added.title: El Paseo en Autobus de Pancake
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín suben a un autobús que da un tour guiado como parte de su plan para recuperar el zapato de Manzana.

added.title: Escondidas
added.description: Unikitty se enorgullece de ser la campeona del Día de la escondida. Pero cuando encuentra a todos en el reino excepto a Richard, lo busca a toda costa. ¿Seguirá Richard eludiendo a la princesa en su juego favorito y, si es así, cómo lo hará?

added.title: Tu Eres Rad
added.description: Cuando K.O. se olvida su chapa identificatoria, Rad le presta la suya, lo cual hace que todos piensen que K.O. es Rad, incluido el mismo Rad.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Pegados
added.description: Cuando la cabeza de Master Frown se atasca en el cuerpo de Unikitty, ella promete ayudarlo a recuperar su antiguo cuerpo, ipero primero, tiene que ocuparse de sus deberes de princesa! Pero compartir un cuerpo con Master Frown puede ser bastante complicado, especialmente cuando él tiene sus propios planes en mente.

added.title: Principito perricornio
added.description: Puppycorn por fin se da cuenta de que es un príncipe, iy quiere estar a cargo del reino por una vez! A pesar de las preocupaciones de sus amigos, Unikitty permite que Puppycorn sea el rey, pero pronto, el poder absoluto en las manos del cachorro se le hace difícil de manejar, y sus ideas no son lo que se diría muy geniales. ¿Podrán removerlo del poder mientras evitan un levantamiento del pueblo?

added.title: Mascota
added.description: Unikitty y la pandilla traen a casa a una pequeña criatura a la que llaman Pet Pet, pero Richard no les permite quedársela si no pueden demostrar que son dueños responsables. Cuando Pet Pet se escapa, Unikitty debe fingir ser la mascota hasta que puedan encontrarlo, io Richard nunca les dejará tener a Pet Pet (o a cualquier mascota) de nuevo! ¿Sobrevivirá Unikitty al entrenamiento de mascotas, o terminará admitiendo que la responsabilidad es mucho más difícil de lo que pensaba?

added.title: Juicio Gatuno
added.description: Cuando Unikitty tiene un pequeño incidente automovilístico con Master Frown, iél insiste en llevar el tema a juicio! Frown está encantado: no hay nada peor que un tribunal viejo y aburrido, y está ansioso por someter a Unikitty a esa experiencia. A Unikitty le gusta hacer las cosas bien, pero el juicio se realizará en la corte de Unikitty, ique es tan absurda y divertida que se convierte en la peor pesadilla de Frown! ¿Master Frown logrará contagiar a Unikitty con su negatividad? ¿O será él quien termine castigado por las payasadas legales?

added.title: Dream Boat
added.description: Sumo devotes himself to the Sisyphean task of building a boat, defying the expectations of everyone in his life, including himself.

added.title: Video Cita
added.description: Panda es un ávido salidor de citas por Internet, y cuando una adorable mujer francesa coincide con él y accede a tener una cita virtual con video, Panda y sus hermanos manejan la situación para poder mostrar su mejor perfil en el video, aunque ese perfil sea absolutamente exagerado.

added.title: Hoyo En 10
added.description: Mientras Ben juega al minigolf, lo atacan los Ground Hawgs, una pandilla de mutantes convertidos en ciclistas del Doctor Ánimo. Pero cuando los Hawgs se dan cuenta de que la falsa aldea de minigolf no es un lugar real, Ben debe transformarse en alienígena para detenerlos antes de que elijan la ciudad verdadera que está a pocos metros de allí como su blanco.

added.title: Neighborhood Grill
added.description: Clarence is so troubled by the sight of his teacher in a social setting outside of school, he can't stop himself from intruding on her doomed blind date.

added.title: Receta Del Desastre
added.description: Durante el festival gastronómico Chefapalooza en las Montañas Rocosas, el Tri-Chefta, compuesto por tres cocineros famosos y villanos infames, persigue a Wildvine con la esperanza de crear el plato más exótico que jamás hayan preparado.

added.title: Descanse En Paz Rustbucket
added.description: Durante un tour por la histórica ciudad de Oldeville, Ben encuentra una carta de Sumo Slammers poco común. Pero cuando Billy Billones reclama esa carta, Ben debe luchar contra los drones tecnológicos de Billy, ique secuestraron la Chatarra!

added.title: Chloe Y Polar
added.description: Un día, Chloe sale sola a pasear con Polar y se da cuenta de que Polar se la pasa haciéndoles recados a sus hermanos. Decidida a mostrarle cómo pasarla bien en la ciudad, Chloe promete ayudar a que Polar se divierta... Aunque eso signifique quedarse dentro de un museo después de la hora de cierre.

added.title: Segunda Primer Cita
added.description: El amor flota en el aire, y Cupido llega para resolver la tensión romántica de la plaza.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Gwen O Ben
added.description: Cuando Ben interfiere con la misión de Hex -el mago malicioso- para los Titan Gloves, que hacen tareas de movimiento de tierra en un centro de trueque, Hex intercambia el cuerpo de Ben con el de Gwen, lo cual lo obliga a caminar un kilómetro y medio en sus zapatos iy viceversa!

added.title: Ben 24 Horas
added.description: Cuando Ben (iy Gwen!) intenta quedarse despierto toda la noche para ir a Adrenaland -el único parque temático abierto las 24 horas, los siete días de la semana- no solo es incapaz de utilizar sus poderes alienígenas para lograr su objetivo, sino que además su estado de adormecimiento alienígena provoca un desastre tras otro, y Gwen debe arreglar las cosas antes de que todo se salga de control.

added.title: A rad le gustan los robots
added.description: Rad encuentra el amor en un lugar inesperado.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Tiger and Mouse
added.description: An unlikely friendship between Giant Realistic Flying Tiger and a mouse threatens to destroy everything inside the RV.

added.title: Pizza Steve's Diary
added.description: When his diary winds up in the hands of Mr. Gus, Pizza Steve goes to great lengths to get it back before Mr. Gus can read all of his deepest, darkest secrets.

added.title: Ballin'
added.description: Uncle Grandpa, Pizza Steve, and Mr. Gus must win a basketball game against a super awesome b-ball crew in order to keep the RV.

added.title: Big Trouble for Tiny Miracle
added.description: Tiny Miracle allows the gang to take advantage of his generosity at the expense of his own health.

removed.title: Crushing Defeat
removed.description: When Hawkodile develops a secret crush on Dr. Fox, he finds himself actually crushing down in size! With Hawkodile too embarrassed to tell her (or anyone) about it, Unikitty and the gang become his love gurus to help him confess his feelings before he shrinks away into nothing!

removed.title: The Great Bongo Heist
removed.description: The boys forget to get Chata a gift for Abuela Day and in a panicked move, they pretend that the bongo drums they borrowed from Xochi are for her. Knowing they have to return the drums, Victor & Valentino pretend to be burglars to steal the bongos back.

removed.title: The Power of Shrimps
removed.description: Aqualad uses shrimps and prime rib to win back Raven.

removed.title: Sibling Rivalry
removed.description: When a new robot, Raymond, defeats the three heroes to steal the sign to Gar's, KO teams up with Darrell and Shannon to get it back.

removed.title: Matched
removed.description: When a computer dating program matches Beast Boy to Raven, he tries wooing her to disastrous effect.

removed.title: Soy Dendy
removed.description: K.O. ayuda a Dendy, una niña extraña de la escuela, a conseguir las piezas que necesita para reparar su mochila de alta tecnología.
removed.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

removed.title: Terra-ized
removed.description: Beast Boy falls for Terra despite clear signs that she is more interested in destroying the Titans.

removed.title: Cellie
removed.description: Fed up with sharing, Panda forbids his brothers from using his cellphone any longer. But when the brothers get their own super advanced smartphones, Panda starts to succumb to crippling jealousy.

removed.title: Incendium
removed.description: Jake sets Finn up with the Flame Princess with fiery results.

removed.title: Secrets
removed.description: Grandpa Max's mysterious past comes to light when Vilgax shows up on earth in search of the Omnitrix. And the family must work together to defeat him.

removed.title: Aluxes
removed.description: When Vic finds an ancient relic that summons a gang of mischievous creatures, he uses them to do his bidding, which has disastrous consequences.

removed.title: Tips
removed.description: Apple and Onion have to find a way to ride the Hot Air Balloon which is in their town for one day only.

removed.title: A Fistful of Brains
removed.description: Grandpa Max and Rook are looking all over the galaxy for Ben, who is trapped on Khyber's hidden personal hunting preserve.

removed.title: The Kiss
removed.description: Gumball is traumatised when accidentally kissed on the mouth by his Grandma JoJo.

removed.title: The Shell
removed.description: Gumball inadvertently cracks open Penny's shell and discovers who she really is inside . . . While performing a school play, Gumball is so nervous about kissing Penny that he accidentally headbutts her and cracks open her shell. They discover that under Penny's shell is an emotional shape-shifting inner self. Penny's father is determined for Penny to keep it hidden but Gumball encourages her to show the world who, or what, she really is . . .

removed.title: I Am Dendy
removed.description: KO helps a strange girl from school, Dendy, get the parts she needs to repair her high tech backpack.

removed.title: Conduciendo A La Locura
removed.description: Cuando la Chatarra se rompe en un parque de casas rodantes, Ben descubre que se encuentran en la última etapa del Cali 10 Hundred-una carrera de autos épica todo terreno-en la que LaGrange, el piloto demente, ha regresado en busca de venganza contra aquellos que lo descalificaron hace años.
